Water Recharge Clause: 
For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

(iv)	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Premises.

Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase or Work Relocation)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house or are relocating due to work. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase or work relocation necessitates the termination.

1.	Rent in advance

Further to clause B5 and B6 of this Agreement it is further agreed that the tenant Darja Wischerath and Ryan Famiglietti shall pay their rent for the first 6 months of this Agreement in one sum payable in advance on the signing of this Agreement. At the end of the first 6 month period  Darja Wischerath and Ryan Famiglietti agree to pay a further 6 months rent in advance installments until the end of the tenancy. These sums shall be paid on or before the  16/08/2022 and the 16/12/2022, 16/08/2023, 16/12/2023 and not on the first of the month as expressed in Clause B5. At the end of this tenancy, should the tenant seek a New Agreement and should the Landlord agree to this, the tenant agrees to pay for further referencing to determine whether they can pay monthly in advance for the new term whether as a result of the referencing the Landlord shall require them to pay in advance for whole term. In either case the tenant Darja Wischerath and Ryan Famiglietti undertakes to comply with the Landlord or his agents` instructions with regard payment and to make such payment promptly and inline with the provisions of this Agreement.

PET CLAUSE

The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a cat on the Property provided that 
i.	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
ii.	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage
iii.	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
iv.	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property

Military Break Clause 

Notwithstanding the express terms contained herein this Tenancy may be terminated earlier by the Tenant for reasons of military necessity, further defined below, subject to the Tenant giving the Landlord/Agent not less than thirty (30) days’ notice in writing, such written notice to be served personally or by Recorded Delivery Post by the Tenant upon the Landlord/Agent. Military necessity generally includes but is not limited to the following circumstances: The Tenant is officially directed by the United States Air Force to a permanent duty location that is at least ten (10) miles greater in distance from the leased premises than the Tenant’s duty location was when the Tenancy was entered into, this includes Permanent Change of Station (PCS) and Permanent Change of Assignment (PCA); or The Tenant is directed by the United States Air Force to occupy quarters or accommodations provided by the United States Air Force or its agents; or The Tenant, their spouse and/or dependents are no longer permitted to remain in England of Wales, or are required to return to the United States (or place of origin other than England or Wales) for a protracted period of time (e.g. loss of command sponsorship, military necessity, illness or death); of if the United Kingdom or the United States become party to a war; or The Tenant is directed to deploy to temporary duty location for a period in excess of ninety (90) days; or The Tenant leaves the United States military or civilian service for any reason. Additionally, the Tenant may terminate this Tenancy early if the Tenant voluntarily accepts an offer of accommodation provided by the United States Air Force or its agents, subject to the Tenants having resided at the Property for at least (6) months of this Tenancy. The Tenant must give the landlord/agent not less than thirty (20) days’ notice of termination under this clause in writing, such written notice to be served personally or by Recorded Delivery post of the Tenant upon the Landlord/Agent. If the Tenant property effects notice of early termination under this clause, the Landlord/Agent shall not request from the Tenant any charge, levy, penalty, or other payment whatsoever by reason of such termination.

special_clause_free_text__c:
GUARANTEE AND INDEMNITY

25 April 2024

BETWEEN

1.	Mrs Claire Bruce-Lamblin of 13 Upper Phillimore Gardens, London, W8 7HF (“the Guarantor”) and

2.	Miss Aurelia Adler 22/3 London Street, Edinburgh, EH3 6NA (“the Tenant”) and

3.	Grainger Pearl (Salford) Limited.of Grainger PLC, Citygate, St. James Boulevard, Newcastle upon Tyne, Tyne and Wear, NE1 4JE (“the Landlord”)


It is agreed as follows: 
In consideration of the Landlord granting a lease of (”the Premises”) Flat 32 Wilbraham House Wandsworth Road London SW8 2XD to the Tenant dated 4th May 2024 (“the Lease”) at a rent of £2,500.00 per calendar month (“the Rent”) payable in advance on the first day of each month the Guarantor hereby guarantees a 50% payment of the Rent (Miss Aurelia Adler share) and the performance and observance of the tenant’s covenants under the Lease by the Tenant upon the following conditions:

1.	PAYMENT OF RENT IN ARREARS

If the Tenant defaults in the payment of the Rent the Guarantor will pay any arrears of Rent to the Landlord immediately upon receipt of the Landlord’s written demand and including:

1.1 Any increased Rent subsequently agreed between the Landlord and Tenant; and 

1.2 Any mesne profits due to the Landlord for any period during which the Tenant occupies 
the Premises after the end of the contractual term

2.	INDEMNITY FOR DEFAULT OR BREACH OF TENANT OBLIGATIONS 

If the Tenant does not observe or breaches its covenants and obligations under the Lease the Guarantor will indemnify the Landlord immediately upon receipt of the Landlord’s written demand in respect of all losses damages expenses and costs incurred by the Landlord as a result of the Tenant’s default which the Landlord is unable to recover from the Tenant. 

3.	DURATION OF GUARANTEE AND INDEMNITY

3.1 This Guarantee and Indemnity shall continue from the date hereof for the duration of the term granted by the Lease and including any extension of that Lease and any period during which the Tenant occupies the Premises 

3.2 This Guarantee and Indemnity shall not be revocable by the Guarantor nor shall it be discharged by the death of the Guarantor or by the death or bankruptcy or insolvency of the Tenant.

3.3 If the Tenant becomes bankrupt the Guarantor will pay the Rent on the terms and on the dates specified in the Lease for the duration of the term or until the Premises have been re-let by the Landlord, whichever shall happen first. 

3.4	The Guarantor shall not be discharged from its obligations under this Guarantee and Indemnity if the Landlord gives the Tenant additional time in which to pay the Rent or to correct the breaches or defaults of the tenant’s covenants under the Lease. 



4.	JOINT AND SEVERAL LIABILITY 

4.1 It is agreed that the Guarantor’s liability is joint and several with the Tenant which means that each will be responsible for complying with the Tenant’s covenants under the Lease both individually and together.

4.2 The Landlord may seek to enforce these obligations and claim damages against the Tenant the Guarantor or both. 

4.3 Where any party to this Guarantee and Indemnity comprises more than one person the obligations and liabilities of that party under this Guarantee and Indemnity shall be joint and several obligations and liabilities of those persons.

5.	WHEN THE GUARANTEE IS TO CEASE

If the Lease is terminated by agreement between the parties (“the Termination Date”) the Guarantor shall not incur any further liability hereunder after the Termination Date but any liability of the Guarantor to pay any sums accrued up to the Termination Date shall continue. 

6.	NOTICES 

6.1 Any notice or demand to be given under this Guarantee and Indemnity shall be given by sending the same in a pre-paid envelope by recorded delivery or ordinary first-class post or at the address of the receiving party as detailed above or at its last known address. 

6.2 Any such notice or demand shall be deemed served within 48 hours of posting provided that the time deemed for service shall be a business day which for the purposes of this Guarantee and Indemnity will be 9a.m. to 5p.m. on any day other than a Saturday, a Sunday or a Bank Holiday in England and Wales (“Business Day”) 

6.3 Any notice or demand which arrives on any day other than a Business Day shall be deemed to be served on the next Business Day.

7.	MISCELLANEOUS

7.1 The Guarantor acknowledges that she has been informed of his rights to take independent                     
legal advice prior to signing this Guarantee and Indemnity 

7.2 The Guarantor will notify the Landlord of any change of her address.

Military Break Clause

Notwithstanding the express terms contained herein this Tenancy may be terminated earlier by the Tenant for reasons of military necessity, further defined below, subject to the Tenant giving the Landlord/Agent not less than thirty (30) days’ notice in writing, such written notice to be served personally or by Recorded Delivery Post by the Tenant upon the Landlord/Agent.

Military necessity generally includes but is not limited to the following circumstances:
The Tenant is officially directed by the United States Air Force to a permanent duty location that is at least ten (10) miles greater in distance from the leased premises than the Tenant’s duty location was when the Tenancy was entered into, this includes Permanent Change of Station (PCS) and Permanent Change of Assignment (PCA); or The Tenant is directed by the United States Air Force to occupy quarters or accommodations provided by the United States Air Force or its agents; or The Tenant, their spouse and/or dependents are no longer permitted to remain in England of Wales, or are required to return to the United States (or place of origin other than England or Wales) for a protracted period of time (e.g. loss of command sponsorship, military necessity, illness or death); of if the United Kingdom or the United States become party to a war; or The Tenant is directed to deploy to temporary duty location for a period in excess of ninety (90) days; or The Tenant leaves the United States military or civilian service for any reason.

Additionally, the Tenant may terminate this Tenancy early if the Tenant voluntarily accepts an offer of accommodation provided by the United States Air Force or its agents, subject to the Tenants having resided at the Property for at least (6) months of this Tenancy. The Tenant must give the landlord/agent not less than thirty (20) days’ notice of termination under this clause in writing, such written notice to be served personally or by Recorded Delivery post of the Tenant upon the Landlord/Agent. If the Tenant property effects notice of early termination under this clause, the Landlord/Agent shall not request from the Tenant any charge, levy, penalty, or other payment whatsoever by reason of such termination.

In order to end the tenancy early we may serve on you a Section 21 notice at any time after four months from the beginning of the tenancy as set out in Clause B4 of this agreement. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in the Section 21 notice, which will be at least two months from the date of service of the notice

Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase or Work Relocation)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house or are relocating due to work. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase or work relocation necessitates the termination

Consent to Keep a Pet

	The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a cat on the Premises provided that

(i)	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by the pet to the Premises or Contents or to the garden at the Premises or to any neighbouring garden or premises

(ii)	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Premises with one of similar quality that the pet shall soil or damage 

(iii)	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Premises or Contents by the pet which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

(iv)	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Premises.

St Anne’s Water Re-Charge


For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

St Anne’s Water Re-Charge


For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

Consent to Keep a Pet

	The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a pet on the Premises provided that

(i)	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by the pet to the Premises or Contents or to the garden at the Premises or to any neighbouring garden or premises

(ii)	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Premises with one of similar quality that the pet shall soil or damage 

(iii)	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Premises or Contents by the pet which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

(iv)	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Premises.

Consent to Keep a Pet

	The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a pet on the Premises provided that

(i)	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by the pet to the Premises or Contents or to the garden at the Premises or to any neighbouring garden or premises

(ii)	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Premises with one of similar quality that the pet shall soil or damage 

(iii)	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Premises or Contents by the pet which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

(iv)	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Premises.

St Anne’s Water Re-Charge


For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

Consent to Keep a Pet

	The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a pet on the Premises provided that

(i)	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by the pet to the Premises or Contents or to the garden at the Premises or to any neighbouring garden or premises

(ii)	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Premises with one of similar quality that the pet shall soil or damage 

(iii)	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Premises or Contents by the pet which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

(iv)	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Premises.

Tenant Break Clause (House Purchase or Work Relocation)
In order to end the tenancy early you may serve on us written notice at any time where you have purchased a house or are relocating due to work. The tenancy will come to an end on the date referred to in your notice, which must be at least two months from the date of service of the notice. Your notice must be accompanied by documentary evidence demonstrating to our satisfaction (acting reasonably) that the house purchase or work relocation necessitates the termination.

Consent to Keep a Pet

	The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a pet on the Premises provided that

(i)	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by the pet to the Premises or Contents or to the garden at the Premises or to any neighbouring garden or premises

(ii)	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Premises with one of similar quality that the pet shall soil or damage 

(iii)	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Premises or Contents by the pet which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

(iv)	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Premises.

special_clause_free_text__c: The Landlord has agreed that the tenant will have the 7th month rent free as an agreed rent incentive
As part of an 8 week rent incentive, £2,328.44 will be deducted from the initial payment. A further £1,831.56 will be deducted from June's rent.

Rent in Advance
The landlord agrees that the tenant will have 6 weeks rent free at the beginning of the tenancy. £2,831.10 will be deducted from the initial monies owed and £528.90 will be deducted from the rent due on the 1st June, meaning the rent for this period will be £1,897.76, then £2,426.66 on the first of each month for the remainder of the tenancy.


Smoking
You, your family, guests and visitors must not smoke any substance or use electronic cigarettes inside or in the vicinity of the premises or the building, including on any balcony or in any communal spaces and in the event that damage is caused to the premises or the building as a result of a breach of this clause of the agreement, you agree to pay the costs incurred by us, in repairing that damage or redecorating the premises or building or have a sum equal to those costs deducted from the deposit.
Initial Move In Monies to be transferred over from 74 Kew Bridge Court
The Landlord agrees to a 5 week free rent incentive @ £2300 to be deducted from the Initial Moving In Monies.
pet clause

Pet Clause
Further to Clause E39 the Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep 1 Dog on the Property provided that 
(i) the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
(ii) the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage 
(iii) the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
(iv) it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property

1. Rent In Advance Clause - Miss Zenilda Tavares

Further to clause B5 and B6 of this Agreement it is further agreed that the tenant Miss Zenilda Tavares shall pay their rent share for the full 6 months of this Agreement in one sum of £1,950 payable in advance on the signing of this Agreement. At the end of this tenancy should tenant Miss Zenilda Tavares seek a New Agreement and should the Landlord agree to this, the tenant agrees to pay for further referencing to determine whether they can pay monthly in advance for the new term whether as a result of the referencing the Landlord shall require them to pay in advance for whole term. In either case the tenant Miss Zenilda Tavares undertakes to comply with the Landlord or his agents` instructions with regard payment and to make such payment promptly and inline with the provisions of this Agreement
The Landlord agrees to a 1 month free over 12 months for the term of the tenancy.

PET CLAUSE

i.	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
ii.	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage
iii.	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
iv.	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property

11.	SPECIAL CLAUSES

11.1	Smoking

You, your family, guests and visitors must not smoke any substance or use electronic cigarettes inside or in the vicinity of the premises or the building, including on any balcony or in any communal spaces and in the event that damage is caused to the premises or the building as a result of a breach of this clause of the agreement, you agree to pay the costs incurred by us, in repairing that damage or redecorating the premises or building or have a sum equal to those costs deducted from the deposit

11.2	LW Water Re-Charge

For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Thames Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly installments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Thames Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Thames Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property

11.3 Tenant Break Clause

The Landlord agrees that the Tenant has the right to terminate the Tenancy giving the Landlord not less than TWO (2) months PRIOR notice in writing. For the avoidance of doubt between the parties it is agreed that the notice period must expire on the last day of a month (being the day before the next rental payment is due) as detailed in Clause 1.3 of Core Terms.

1.	Parking

The premises                            Parking Bay Numbers: 106 & 104                                             
THE TERM                                 The term set out at clause B4

We licence and permit you to occupy and enjoy the Parking Bay detailed above for the period detailed above. The terms and obligations of both parties are detailed under. 

1.1. Terms and obligations
	
You agree and undertakes as follows:- 

1.1.1     You will relinquish the Parking Bay at any time during the said term upon one month’s written notice from either party.  Such notice is to be in line with the end of a paid license period.
	
1.1.2     You shall keep the Parking Bay in a good state of repair and clean and tidy at all times.
	
1.1.3     You shall not place any signs or advertisement upon the Parking Bay.
	
1.1.4     This Licence is personal to you and you shall not assign sublet or in any way part with or share use of the Parking Bay.
	
1.1.5     The Parking Bay shall be used for the purpose of parking one private motor vehicle only.

1.1.6     You shall not allow any petrol or inflammable liquid or material to be kept on the Parking Bay.

1.1.7     You shall not make any alterations to the Parking Bay.

1.1.8     You shall not cause nuisance or annoyance to us or any other Licensees of the other Parking Bay s at the address of the Premises.

1.1.9     You shall not do anything nor allow anything to be done which might prejudice or invalidate our insurance policy nor increase the premium payable.

1.1.10   Upon termination of this Licence agreement you will deliver up the Parking Bay to the owner in good state of repair and cleaned and swept.

1.1.11   You shall not use the Parking Bay for the storage of other articles or for the purpose of any trade or business.

1.1.12   You shall not cause obstruction to the access to our other Parking Bays or land. 

1.1.13   Where applicable you shall be provided with 1 remote access fobs to be retained for the duration of the license.

1.1.14   You shall provide to the Managing Agents details of your registration number for the vehicle being parked in the Parking Bay and proof of ownership when requested by the our Managing Agent during the term of this License.

1.2.       General Agreements between us and you

1.2.1     Neither we nor our Managing Agents shall be responsible for any loss or damage sustained by you or your vehicle in respect of any neglect default omission of any of our employees nor in respect of any works of repair additional alteration or other works which may be carried on neighbouring premises in our ownership.       

1.2.2	This Licence may be terminated as per the term set out at clause I6.

1.2.3     This Licence shall cease and terminate if you fail to observe and perform any of the obligations on your part contained in this Agreement by notice served by the us upon you.

1.2.4     At the termination of this Licence you shall return any access fobs where appropriate.

1.2.5     If we have served notice to determine this Licence and you do not immediately vacate the said Parking Bay and we must commence legal proceedings to obtain vacant possession of the said Parking Bay then you shall pay to us all costs of any description incurred by us in taking proceedings of any nature whatsoever against you.

St Anne's Water Re-Charge
For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

St Anne’s Water Re-Charge

For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

PET CLAUSE

The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep a dog on the Property provided that 
i.	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by such animal to the Property or Contents or to the garden at the Property or to any neighbouring garden or property 
ii.	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Property with one of similar quality that such animal shall soil or damage
iii.	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Property or Contents by such animal which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy 
iv.	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Property.

St Anne’s Water Re-Charge


For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.

Consent to Keep a Pet

	The Landlord agrees solely for the purpose of this Tenancy that the Tenant may keep one small dog on the Premises provided that

(i)	the Tenant shall pay for any damage caused by the pet to the Premises or Contents or to the garden at the Premises or to any neighbouring garden or premises

(ii)	the Tenant shall pay to the Landlord the cost of replacing any carpet rug fabric or other item in the Premises with one of similar quality that the pet shall soil or damage 

(iii)	the Tenant shall indemnify the Landlord against any related infestation damage and treatment caused to the Premises or Contents by the pet which may become evident during or up to two months after the termination of the Tenancy

(iv)	it is agreed that such consent may be withdrawn by the Landlord during the course of the Tenancy in the event of unreasonable or excessive damage being caused to the Premises.

St Anne’s Water Re-Charge


For any Premises without a separate or individual water meter, you agree to pay such amount as is specified by the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge as is relevant for the size of the Premises. Such annual sum is to be split into monthly instalments and paid during the tenancy term by the same method and on the same dates as the Rent is paid under the terms of this Lease. For the avoidance of doubt, this sum is an amount which must be paid in addition to the Rent. We reserve the right to increase or decrease the payments required under this clause in the event that there are any changes to the Southern Water Assessed Household Charge. If we decide to do this, we will serve you with 30 days written notice of our decision and you agree to pay the new amount from the next date upon which the rent is due after 30 days written notice has been served upon you. In the event that the Southern Water Assessed Water Household Charge ceases to exist, the parties will seek to agree an alternative means to settle water charges at the property.
